The paper proposes a new recurrent autoencoder architecture for online compression of sequential data with temporal dependency. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, given that the paper focuses on speech spectrogram compression, cs.SD is the most likely category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that cs.CL and cs.LG are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of compression techniques, which suggests that cs.IT and cs.AI are also possible categories.
